You are a trusted and recognized leader, consistently demonstrating credibility in cross-functional interactions.<br />
You are a leader with practical design chops. You’ve shipped many consumer products over the years, and understand what it takes to create awesome, consumer-oriented experiences.<br />
You’re a fantastic communicator. You have the communication skills to help you work cross-functionally with business partners.<br />
You shine most at inspiring others to carry forward and execute a strategy without needing to be in the room.<br />
You have a user and data-focused design mentality. You are constantly looking to hone your team’s instincts through user feedback and data insight. You understand the role and importance of qualitative and quantitative methodologies.<br />
You are eager to learn and evolve in all things. From leadership skills to design craft to process to industry and market trends – you never stop pushing into the next big challenge.<br />
You are familiar and comfortable working within and contributing to large design systems that you may or may not own directly. Balancing the needs of the larger design ecosystem with the local goals of your product area.</p>
